Absolutely — here’s a proper exam-ready checklist you can follow in order.

The task brief says Task 1 needs two submissions: a proposal and a set of design documents. The proposal must include business context, requirements, decomposition, KPIs, acceptance criteria, solution description, justification, risk mitigation, and legal/regulatory points. The design documents must include visual/interface designs, data requirements, algorithm designs, and a test strategy.  ￼

The distinction example is useful because it follows a strong structure with sections like Business context, Empathy map, User stories, Functional requirements, Non-functional requirements, Decomposition, KPIs, Description of proposed solution, Justification, Risk mitigation, Legal and regulatory requirements, and Appendices. That is a very good model to copy for your own layout.

Task 1 checklist in the best order

1. Before you start writing

Use this first so you do not miss any exam rules.

