3. Design documents checklist — Activity B

The brief says your design documents must include visual/interface designs, data requirements, algorithm designs, and a test strategy. They also need enough detail for technical and non-technical stakeholders and for a third-party developer to build the solution.

Section 1: Visual/interface designs

Check	Exactly what to do
☐	Create wireframes or mock-ups for the main pages.
☐	Show page layout, buttons, navigation, forms, and key features.
☐	Make it clear enough that another developer could build it.

Best pages to design:
	•	homepage
	•	producers page
	•	product listing
	•	product details
	•	basket
	•	checkout
	•	delivery / collection selection
	•	login / register
