Best heading order to use in your proposal

This is the cleanest order, based on the distinction example and the brief:
	1.	Business Context
	2.	Empathy Map
	3.	User Stories and Acceptance Criteria
	4.	Functional Requirements
	5.	Non-Functional Requirements
	6.	Decomposition
	7.	KPIs
	8.	User Acceptance Criteria
	9.	Description of Proposed Solution
	10.	Justification
	11.	How Risks Will Be Mitigated
	12.	Legal and Regulatory Requirements
	13.	Appendices

Most important thing to remember

Do not just list features. For every section, keep linking back to:
	•	what GLH asked for
	•	what the users need
	•	why your choice is suitable
	•	how it will actually work

That is what the distinction example does well, and that is what will make your work stronger.

